<p>There are an endless number of posts out there giving their perspective on what it takes to be an entrepreneur, how to run a startup, how to succeed, and all of that crap we heard from Tony Robbins.&nbsp; Once you announce you&rsquo;re doing something in the tech world, &nbsp;the hangers come out of the woodwork from all around you.&nbsp; The hardest to avoid are your close friends and family. I have never had a problem separating business from my personal life, and after a recent experience with a close friend and family member, I wanted to outline our world. This is a blog post about being deep in the mud taking grenades that we could point our close friends and family members to before they begin working on their "this could be the next Facebook" idea.&nbsp; If you have read this far, you must think you have the balls to try something new and&nbsp;succeed.&nbsp;
</p>
