<p>One of my favorite lines from this clip is &ldquo;I am here to tell you that most of you want to be successful, but you don&rsquo;t want it bad, you just kinda want it.&rdquo;&nbsp; Success is earned.&nbsp; You have to want it bad, each and every minute of every day.&nbsp; In some cases it&rsquo;s the only reason you may be alive today.&nbsp; You WILL NOT SLEEP.&nbsp; If this bothers you, turn around and run away. Let&rsquo;s be honest, this bus ride is not for everyone.&nbsp; At the end of the day, I am ok with that.&nbsp; We live in one of the greatest countries in the world, and if you want it, you can go out and get it.&nbsp; It will not be easy, and most fail in the process.&nbsp; I am tired of the people who look at the person driving the Bentley and saying, &ldquo;oh he or she must be cheating, must be a trust fund kid, etc.&rdquo; Who fucking cares? Why do you care? My father always taught me to work as hard as I could at everything I set out to do, regardless of what others thought.&nbsp; If they are in your way, run them over, not everyone is meant to sit at same table in your house.&nbsp; You get to choose who those close advisors are. Make sure you pick wisely.&nbsp; You may be reading this and thinking &ldquo;Chris only cares about money!&rdquo;&nbsp; If you are thinking this, than stop reading this, find something better to do with your time.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s not about money, it&rsquo;s about enjoying the journey, the stress, the sacrifice, the time, it&rsquo;s about not sleeping. I recently watched this {% link http://youtu.be/UxjCzSP30wM "video about a bad ass named Kai Greene" %}. &nbsp;</p>
<p>
